description.2: Having let himself be captured by the Troyjans, Bruce Banner infiltrates their headquarters to learn their secrets!
description.5: Captain America, fighting with his trusty team of Avengers, plans to take down Hydra once and for all in this issue!
description.6: Alpha Flight has come to America. Their mission: bring Logan back to Canada. Wolverine has a counter-offer; chances are Alpha Flight won't be too happy about it...
description.10: Choosing the most awesome thing about this issue is really tough! Dr. Doom's first appearance? Thing dressed up as a pirate? Stan Lee and Jack Kirby starting to hit their stride? Epic win.
description.11: Hot-headed Firebrand triggers a dormant volcano. What's a Golden Avenger to do when a few thousand lives are at stake?
description.13: IDENTITY CRISIS! In an effort to keep Spider-Man safe, Peter Parker tries out new identities. Will he be able to keep up the secret or will his true identity be revealed?
description.14: After nearly losing his life against Donald Pierce, Cable accidentally finds himself in Wakanda where he becomes a guest of its monarch…the Black Panther! But a team-up is soon in order, as Ulysses Klaw invades Wakanda seeking its precious vibranium deposits!
description.15: A town of mutant children seems like exactly the kind of place where X-Force can make a difference, but the people of this town don’t want help from anyone!
description.18: Meet Hannibal King! Private eye and...vampire??
description.22: Spider-Man takes on a new identity in order to clear his name! Identity Crisis starts here!
description.23: We're getting closer to a final resolution in the standoff between Grand Admiral Thrawn's forces and the heroes of the New Republic. Feints and counter-feints abound as Thrawn attempts to outguess the New Republic's Bilbringi attack strategy. Meanwhile, Jedi Master C'baoth is confident that he will end up the biggest winner in this battle...
description.24: The all-new'Rogue Squadron'debuts in action in this battle-filled chapter! It's all coming to a head- the'Rebels, now discovered by the'Empire, are fighting for their lives in space, while on the planet'Phaeda,'Carnor Jax'and his personal guard of'stormtroopers'search for'Kir Kanos!'
description.29: Human replica droid Guri has located the only one potentially capable of altering her assassin-driven programming, the surgical droid known as Doc. But now she's being pursued by a bounty hunter, Kar Yang. Savan, working in disguise as a Human female, is trying to secure her hold on the Black Sun organization -- and realizes that Guri is the key. Luke, Han, and Leia, who are meeting with Savan on Coruscant in order to work out a peaceful end to the tumultuous turnover in Black Sun, have no idea who she really is, though.
description.30: The Moff Leonia Tavira has returned, and Rogue Squadron is about to learn just how vindictive some teenagers can be! The woman known as "Iceheart" may have the Empire in her grasp, but Sate Pestage, the interim Emperor, is defecting to the Alliance, and as an example of negotiating in good faith, he offers them the keys to the Imperial Throneworld, Coruscant!
description.32: Nina, now under The Hand's control, attempts to take out her former friend. Will Elektra convince Nina to join her in Kuroyama's undoing?
description.34: Attack of the Troyjans! An army of robots is invading Earth, but how can the Hulk fight back when they've taken his friends hostage?
description.37: New York City has gone Captain America crazy! Cap and his pal, Hawkeye, roam the streets of New York as people fawn over the Cap. However, things take a turn when Batroc the Leaper arrives to fight Captain America for the prestige.
description.38: After draining Wolverine's lifeforce, Sauron attacks the X-Men!
description.39: Wolverine versus Bloodscream and Roughouse! Will Logan's soul remain intact after this brutal battle for the ages?
description.44: The Fantastic Four set off for Canada to help an old friend - the mysteriously ill Silver Surfer!
description.46: Sand and Water mix into quite a muddy situation for our Spider-Man…It's a Sandman and Hydro-Man smack down with a Spider in the middle!
description.47: Can even the Invincible Iron Man stand alone against a squad of the deadly killing machines known as Dreadnoughts?
description.48: HYDE IN MANHATTAN! Mr. Hyde comes back to track down the New World Order and get the money they owed him but encounters his old partner the Cobra, during a brawl. Spider-man watches from afar with a target still on his back. MJ worries and together they try to come up with a new identity in order to keep Spider-Man and his city safe.
description.49: Cable thought he could close the door on the “Hellfire Hunt” saga…but now Apocalypse is lurking in the shadows!
description.50: Black Widow goes undercover to infiltrate Freedom's Light from within!
description.52: Domino is fighting to prove herself worthy of being the bodyguard of a notorious crime boss, but things get complicated when her next opponent is Shatterstar, who’s fighting to save Rictor!
description.57: Continuing the adaptation of the sequel to Star Wars: Dark Force Rising. Adapted from the best-selling Bantam novel by Timothy Zahn, with fantastic art by a pair of Russ Manning Award-winners, Edvin Biukovic, and Eric Shanower.
description.58: The'Rebels'recover from last issue's'Imperial'attack and are forced to abandon their secret base, but not before they deal with'Tem Merkon, the traitor in their midst! And if they thought an attack by the'Empire'was bad, wait till they find out that the evil'Carnor Jax'and his elite'stormtroopers have arrived, and he's after the'Rebel'leader,'Mirith Sinn!'
description.59: Human replica droid Guri continues her quest to discover just how Human she really is. She braves the dangers of the tropical planet Murninkam looking for the surgical droid known as Doc, who has been abducted by Spinda Caveel, a brilliant but more-than-slightly mad scientist, and his deadly cohorts, the Pikkel Sisters. Meanwhile, bounty hunter Kar Yang is hot on the trail of Guri at the request of the shadowy Azool, who wants Guri for reasons that will finally become clear in this issue.
description.65: There are few occupations that are more dangerous than flying an X-wing for the Rebel Alliance, and Rogue Squadron is about to discover that in diplomacy things-and diplomats-are not always what they seem!
description.66: Deacon Frost has taken over New Orleans’ Mafia…and Marie Laveau is his wing woman in evil! Dracula’s reign as Lord of Vampires takes a dangerous turn- one that involves the capture of Blade, Hannibal King, and Brother Voodoo!
description.68: Shang-Chi and the Kingpin feature in Elektra's bid to build a new life!
description.69: The team run into some old friends, but old enemies show up as well and they have their sights set on Dani Moonstar!
description.72: EVERYONE'S AFTER SPIDEY!! Being framed for a death, Spider-man searches for Normie Osborn who has been kidnapped by the Green Goblin. Black Tarantula requests permission to bring his operations to the city and Fortunato, spurning the Rose, allows him in exchange for Spidey's head. Tarantula spares Spidey when he learns he is looking for Normie but takes half of his mask as a prize.
description.73: Cable takes on heavy fire from the Hellfire Club per special request by Sebastian Shaw and the Inner Circle!
description.75: SPIDER-HUNT starts here! It seems that everybody has turned against the Neighborhood Wall-Crawler! Violent thug Override may prove Spidey’s final solution!
description.76: The attempts on Tony Stark's life continue. Plus, witness the return of the deadly Dreadnoughts!
description.78: Bruce and Betty - reunited at last! The military - complacent with the Hulk! Is this a peaceful new beginning for Hulk? Or is there something sinister lurking in the shadows?
description.81: Nobody can locate Captain America's shield in the depths of the Atlantic Ocean! Will he be able to fight the evil Hydra without his most trusted weapon?
description.82: The team comes across the power-drained body of Wolverine. And standing over the body is Rogue. Is she truly to blame?
description.87: Mister Fantastic vs. the Super-Apes! When Reed decides to investigate a mysterious phone call coming from Empire State College, he's forced into a showdown with the Red Ghost and his super-smart simians! Can Reed take the apes alone before they release deadly nerve toxins?
description.88: One woman up against Freedom's Light, a burgeoning terrorist organization? We like Black Widow's odds!
description.90: Mirith Sinn's band of'Rebels'is under siege by the'Empire'as their hideout is discovered! But who should come to their rescue but...Kir Kanos, the last member of the'Crimson Guard! Is he on their side, or is there another reason he is fighting with them? This issue finally reveals just why the Empire is after Kanos, and why Kanos is after'Carnor Jax, the Imperial'who covets the Empire's throne! Plus, at last, you'll learn just what happened to the Crimson Guard after the death of the'Emperor'in'Empire's End!
description.91: Xizor, the leader of the Black Sun organization, has been destroyed, and Guri, a Human replica droid and Xizor's personal assassin, is left wondering what her future will hold now that she no longer has anyone to answer to. Throughout the ongoing struggle for underworld supremacy, Guri endeavors to uncover hints of her Human side - if it even exists. Her search first takes her to the far side of the Rim looking for droid programming genius Massad Thrumble, in the hope that he can alter her programming.
description.97: Approaching the midpoint of the climactic story in Timothy Zahn's exciting Thrawn series, all the story lines are moving toward a convergence: the scheming smugglers, Mara Jade's mysterious past, Grand Admiral Thrawn's plans for using clones to help defeat the New Republic, and Leia's growing concern for the protection of her newborn twins.
description.98: Corellia may have somehow managed to avoid the devastating war between the Empire and the Rebel Alliance, but the back streets of Coronet City have their own brand of villains, and Rogue Squadron can be as heroic on the ground as they are in the sky!

0.text: Karen Page is on trial for the death of a police officer! Mr. Fear is working against her testimony, doing all he can to put Karen behind bars. Can Daredevil cope with the imprisonment of his love? Will Attorney Matt Murdock rise to Karen's defense?

1.text: Kitty Pryde and Peter Wisdom's fraught relationship takes center stage. Will this X-romance continue?

3.text: Peter Parker is undergoing an “Identity Crisis,” and a run-in with the Trapster and Shocker doesn’t make things any easier.

7.text: An investigation into Wolverine's autopsy leads to the discovery of an alien race out to conquer Earth!

8.text: SPIDER-MAN NO MORE! With the web-slinger being hunted as New York City's most wanted, Peter Parker needs a new identity to continue his crime-fighting and clear Spidey's name! Enter: the PRODIGY!

9.text: It's execution day for the Thunderbolts, but Meteorite's got a plan. Will it save the Thunderbolts or simply her own skin?

10.text: Choosing the most awesome thing about this issue is really tough! Dr. Doom's first appearance? Thing dressed up as a pirate? Stan Lee and Jack Kirby starting to hit their stride? Epic win.

12.text: Experience Generation X as you have never before through the Underground mind of Jim Mahfood!

14.text: After nearly losing his life against Donald Pierce, Cable accidentally finds himself in Wakanda where he becomes a guest of its monarch…the Black Panther! But a team-up is soon in order, as Ulysses Klaw invades Wakanda seeking its precious vibranium deposits!

19.text: Alpha Flight is called into action to save the X-Men…all of whom have been kidnapped by Hydra!

20.text: In this flashback issue Quicksilver engages in an old-fashioned duel with Black Knight…all for the love of Crystal! A retrospective featuring Pietro’s history with his Inhuman wife. Which man, (if any), will Crystal choose? Her estranged, impatient husband, or Black Knight, the honored Avenger?

21.text: Ka-Zar continues to lose control over the Savage Land as Shanna's powers grow to a dangerous level!

25.text: A psychotic cop in league with Mr. Fear is stirring up trouble. This corrupt cop has targeted Foggy Nelson’s sister…for death! Daredevil must save an innocent life before time runs out.

28.text: Captain America must train his newly-freed friends to act in an Iron Man-lead attack on Morgan. But when the heroes are forced to battle their ensorcelled teammates, will they be willing to see this battle to the end?

31.text: The Heroes require backup when rescuing a scientist from the clutches of Silver Sable and her Wild Pack. Enter Deadpool? Will this be a decision Luke Cage and Iron Fist come to regret?

32.text: Nina, now under The Hand's control, attempts to take out her former friend. Will Elektra convince Nina to join her in Kuroyama's undoing?

33.text: Nightmare brings a waking hell to Excalibur. Good night and happy deathdreams, X-team!

35.text: What does a cosmic enemy like Blastaar want with a Friendly Neighborhood Wall-Crawler? Find out here.

40.text: When Wolverine investigates a string of murders at Salem Center, all signs point to Maggott!

41.text: Cute and cuddly…not so much. Spidey learns to be wary of the White Rabbit!

42.text: The ‘Cosmic Messiah’ has an agenda all its own, one that involves converting life on Earth into energy. The Thing guest-stars!

43.text: The Thunderbolts are transported to Kosmos!

45.text: Ka-Zar seeks the help of the High Evolutionary to contain Shanna’s power from the terraformer.

49.text: Cable thought he could close the door on the “Hellfire Hunt” saga…but now Apocalypse is lurking in the shadows!

51.text: It’s up to Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver to singlehandedly save New Attitlan! Maximus has mind-controlled his way to a plot of destruction. Will the Inhumans finally see through his jig?  A rollicking adventure from Marvel’s most dynamic sibling duo!

56.text: The Askani'son investigates a S.H.I.E.L.D. clinic where the cyborg-esque Bastion is being held for observation. But Machine Man crashes the scene, and he seems to take a distinctly unfavorable view of the mutant Cable! The story continues in Machine Man/Bastion Annual (1998) #1!

60.text: The Avengers are trapped in strange medieval reality in which they are the playthings of Morgan. But Captain America and Hawkeye have broken the witch's spell and must free their teammates. Meanwhile, Wonder Man is summoned!

61.text: Daredevil tries to solve the mystery of Mr. Fear, but only finds a few questionable characters. Meanwhile, Charlie listens to his killer instincts on Candice. Can Daredevil get to the core of Fear himself?

66.text: Deacon Frost has taken over New Orleans’ Mafia…and Marie Laveau is his wing woman in evil! Dracula’s reign as Lord of Vampires takes a dangerous turn- one that involves the capture of Blade, Hannibal King, and Brother Voodoo!

67.text: Old friends Iron Fist and Luke Cage can’t see eye-to-eye in their treatment of Punisher. Who will win out in the end? Meanwhile, White Tiger and Thena make their triumphant escape from Exodus!

68.text: Shang-Chi and the Kingpin feature in Elektra's bid to build a new life!

73.text: Cable takes on heavy fire from the Hellfire Club per special request by Sebastian Shaw and the Inner Circle!

74.text: Ka-Zar takes home field advantage against Thanos in the SAVAGE LAND!

77.text: The Bamfs and Nightmare combine for a long night of survival for Excalibur!

79.text: Guest-starring Punisher! Spider-Man is pulled into a “spider-hunt” when he becomes the criminal world’s Most Wanted.

83.text: The X-Men’s New Year is rudely interrupted by Sabra, who is out for Magneto's blood!

84.text: Spider-Man, hunted by most of New York, fights the new Green Goblin for the life of the kidnapped Normie Osborn!

85.text: Return from the grave! With the aid of occult magic, Surfer is back in the Land of the Living! But does that mean Mephisto is close behind?

86.text: With the Avengers and the Fantastic Four controlled by Baron Zemo, the Thunderbolts are the only ones left to save the world!

89.text: Quicksilver finds himself in dire straits when he becomes prisoner to the Inhumans! Will Maximus the Mad finally succeed in Pietro’s destruction? Scarlet Witch and Crystal stage a breakout for Luna, held captive by Medusa!

93.text: The Avengers are reunited! As the founding members come together to discuss the recent wave of attacks on former teammates, Thor interrupts the proceedings with grave news: Asgard is in ruins, the Twilight Sword has been taken...doom awaits Midgard!

94.text: Daredevil’s looking for answers about Mr. Fear’s riot at Ryker’s Island. When his hunt takes him to a warden’s house, another vigilante’s already inside! Ghost Rider is on the case, and blames Daredevil for the renewed evil in New York City. A motorcycle race ensues to catch a corrupt warden!

99.text: With Danny leaving the H4H, the rest of the team meets at Oracle Inc. to greet their new lawyer - the Incredible She-Hulk!
